text: Jacquelyn Suzanne GaydaJackie Haas at Big Apple Convention (born November 3, 1981) is an American retired professional wrestler and valet. She is best known for wrestling with World Wrestling Entertainment (WWE) and Total Nonstop Action Wrestling (TNA). She won the second season of Tough Enough. She was married to Charlie Haas from 2005 to 2020. ==Championships and awards== *World Wrestling Entertainment **Tough Enough II (with Linda Miles) *Total Nonstop Action Wrestling **Knockout of the Year in 2005 *Wrestling Observer Newsletter awards **Worst Worked Match of the Year in 2002 (with Christopher Nowinski vs. Bradshaw and Trish Stratus on Raw on July 7). ==References== Category:1981 births Category:Living people Category:American professional wrestlers Category:Female professional wrestlers Category:Former WWE wrestlers Category:Professional wrestling managers and valets Category:Sportspeople from Ohio Category:Total Nonstop Action Wrestling alumni
